You know that we have an algo that seeks text/qualitative feedback when it
sees something interesting that would benefit from context?

At the moment it is optimised to benefit the individual - i.e. it looks at
each individual and figures out where text feedback would be useful.

I realised that I could overlay another frame and add questions that are
designed to generate text feedback that would help an organisation
understand how and why its behaviours are changing. i.e. the algo would look
at how the culture data is changing, figure out the constituent individual
behaviour changes that are driving that culture change and ask for text
examples of how the behaviours have changed when a reviewer identifies such
a change.

Think this will be particularly interesting for D&I (and Bechtel) - as we
will be able to tell them quantitively how their D&I behaviours are changing
but also give them qualitative insight into why those behaviours are
changing.

Not sure I can mock it up until I have some real data to work with but will
be relatively easy to do once I have data and time.

Did I mention that we need some funding quickly?

C


